Citation.sAbstract: The temperature-induced phase behavior of a ternary system consisting of two fluorinated solvents and an organic solvent was studied. The solubility data and liquid liquid equilibrium data for the following ternary systems were examined: (FC3283 + HFE7300 + hexane) at 273.15 K and 298.15 K, (FC3283 + HFE7500 + octane) at 298.15 K and 313.15 K, (FC72 + HFE7100 + acetonitrile) at 273.15 K and 298.15 K, and (FC72 + HFE7100 + ethyl acetate) at 273.15 K and 298.15 K. In addition, the experimental tie line data for eight ternary systems were correlated using the NRTL and UNIQUAC models, and the corresponding binary interaction parameters were determined.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid Liquid Equilibria for the Ternary Systems of FC3283 + HFE7300 + Hexane, FC3283 + HFE7500 + Octane, and FC72 + HFE7100 + (Acetonitrile or Ethyl Acetate) at 273.15 K, 298.15 K, and 313.15 K
